The paper focuses on the security of anonymity networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attacks presented in the paper are based on changes and patterns over time in the network structure and client behavior, which are aspects of network dynamics (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of real-world datasets, which suggests a data science aspect (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of temporal dynamics on anonymity, which could be considered a systems and information aspect (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with privacy and anonymity, which could be categorized under cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
